33.body:
Well, I'm biased towards inflammatory bowel disease since that's the disease I have. And we have some evidence that ingested microplastics damage the gut and cause inflammation.

&#x200B;

[https://particleandfibretoxicology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12989-020-00387-7#:\~:text=Microplastic%20fibres%20and%20fragments%20caused,of%20superoxide%20dismutase%20%5B59%5D](https://particleandfibretoxicology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12989-020-00387-7#:~:text=Microplastic%20fibres%20and%20fragments%20caused,of%20superoxide%20dismutase%20%5B59%5D).

&#x200B;

As I've said before, we need more research on this. But it does seem plausible that this could be one reason why we have increasing chronic disease rates. Of course, poor diet and lifestyle are probably the main factors overall, I'm not disputing that. But exposure to various "unnatural" compounds such as plastics and PFAS does seem to cause problems in the research we have so far.

