Not really, it's like believing that grey marbles are inherently faster and better than any other kind of marbles. There's not a single diversity practice that completely forbids hiring ANY white males.

&#x200B;

And also, this assumes that the person who judges the speed of the marble is objective and only looks at the measurements, not the color. Meanwhile in reality, anonymized resumes and blind hiring practices consistently increase the number of female and minority applicants that get callbacks http://192.248.56.27:8080/jspui/bitstream/123456789/2465/2/A%20Study%20of%20Conceptual%20Framework%20of%20Blind.pdf https://conference.iza.org/conference_files/Eval2012/le%20barbanchon_t4613.pdf  . Be it with orchestra auditions  https://cos.gatech.edu/facultyres/Diversity_Studies/Goldin_Orchestrating%20Impartiality.pdf , or with Hubble Space Telescope  https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/1538-3873/ab6ce0 , or pretty much any other study on the matter.
